03520nam a22004935i 9780292760615DE-B159720240306123113.0m|||||o||d||||||||cr || ||||||||240306t20142014txu    fo  d z      eng d  a97802927606157 a10.7560/7284932doi  a(DE-B1597)587474  a(OCoLC)1286807040  aDE-B1597bengcDE-B1597erda0 aeng  atxucUS-TX 7aGAR0000002bisacsh04a635.96471 aGarrett, Howard, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut10aOrganic Lawn Care :bGrowing Grass the Natural Way /cHoward Garrett. 1aAustin : bUniversity of Texas Press, c[2014] 4c©2014  a1 online resource (168 p.)  atextbtxt2rdacontent  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  atext filebPDF2rda00tFrontmatter -- tContents -- tPreface -- tIntroduction -- tChapter 1. Soil -- tChapter 2. Turfgrasses -- tChapter 3. Lawn Establishment -- tChapter 4. Maintaining the Lawn -- tChapter 5. Products for Lawn Care -- tChapter 6. Alternatives to Lawn Grasses and Turf -- tAppendix -- tIndex0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aA lush green lawn is one of the great pleasures of the natural world, whether it’s right outside your front door or on a majestic fairway at a legendary golf course. But anyone who has tried to grow the perfect lawn the conventional way knows it requires an endless cycle of watering and applying synthetic fertilizers and toxic chemical pesticides that costs a lot of money and kills all the life in the soil, on the surface, and on the grass. Fortunately, there’s a better way. Organic lawn care is not only healthier for the environment, it’s actually cheaper and less water-intensive, whether you’re managing a small yard or acres of turf. In Organic Lawn Care: Growing Grass the Natural Way, Howard Garrett, the renowned “Dirt Doctor,” takes you step-by-step through creating and maintaining turf organically. He begins with the soil, showing you how to establish a healthy habitat for grass. Then he discusses a variety of turfgrasses, including Bermudagrass, bluegrass, buffalograss, fescue, ryegrass, St. Augustine, and zoysia. Garrett explains in detail how to establish and maintain a lawn, including planting, mowing, watering, fertilizing, composting, and managing weeds and pests. And he offers alternatives to lawn grasses and turf, describing the situations in which they might be your best choice. Follow the program in Organic Lawn Care, and don’t be surprised when your water bill drops dramatically and your lawn or golf course is the best-looking one around.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aLawns. 0aOrganic gardening. 0aTurfgrasses. 7aGARDENING / General.2bisacsh0 cprintz978029272849340uhttps://doi.org/10.7560/72849340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780292760615423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780292760615/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles